<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="148" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="148">
This new species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Apotrechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Apotrechus nigrigeniculatus" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrigeniculatus">Apotrechus nigrigeniculatus</taxonomicName>
Liu &amp; Yin, 2002, but differs mainly in the the latter in body larger and subgenital plate of female with hind margin slightly concave.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
